cs.SC, cs.NA, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.CG 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is the most likely category as the paper deals with solving a parameterized polynomial system using algebraic methods and implementing a probabilistic algorithm based on Maple and FGb. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is also likely as the paper discusses computing discriminants and real solutions of polynomial systems. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper presents an algorithm for computing data-discriminants of likelihood equations. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper applies the algorithm to a 3 by 3 symmetric matrix model. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with classifying parameters based on the number of real/positive solutions of a polynomial system.
